When I was 18 my parents, for my Birthday, said that they would pay for me and a +1 to go anywhere in the world for a week. At the time I was so scarred of flying and hadn’t flown in 3 years. The option was to catch the train to somewhere I had been before, or to face my fear and go to a place that was close but where I had always wanted to go, Rome. It was then that my desire to live and explore trumped my fear of flying and dying, so I went. I was terrified but after flying to Rome and back I started to fly again, not that often at first and it was hard. But then I flew more and more, until now when I actually enjoy it. Going to Rome changed my life and was definately one of the best things I ever did, I truely love this city, it really is a historical masterpiece ğŸ’•

node.text:
Day one of moving into our apartment I started to feel really sick. It started off with a migraine and a few moments of throwing up and as the days went on it’s been cold/flu symptoms. I’ve been fighting fevers of 102.0 and a little lower, having congestion to a point I can’t breathe and coughing to a point I start throwing up. I don’t feel that great but despite all that bad I’m happy because I have a place to call home. I have an amazing friend, Dee, who sent me this adorable welcome package (picture 1) and my bestie/roommate bought me Halloween socks and gave them to me after we moved in (2), I’ve been on a diet of soup, tea, Gatorade and water all week with the occasional let’s attempt to eat real food which results in me being sicker ğŸ¤¦‍â™€ï¸ and I’ve gotten to rest and watch glee and halloween stuff. While I miss being at work and hate being sick I’m trying not to move too much and get myself sicker. Rest is important and I hope y’all are staying safe out there and resting as well when needed be. Let this post be a reminder that covid is very much so real and it may or may not be what I have but either way, stay home if you can. Wear masks. Hydrate. Don’t forget to eat and treat yourself to breaks when you need them. Stay safe everyone. â¤ï¸â¤ï¸â¤ï¸

BÃ¡nh bá»™t lá»c is a tapioca dumpling similar to some crystal dumplings found in dim sum. They are a popular street food that can be found steamed in banana leaves. The texture of the dumping is a chewy thick skin but packed with tons of flavor. A very unique mouthfeel ğŸ¤¤
.
.

Filling: 
1 lb deveined shrimp cut into bite size pieces
1 tbsp annatto oil
4 garlic cloves
1 tbsp minced shallot
1/2 tbsp sugar 
1/2 tbsp paprika
2 tbsp fish sauce 
Salt and pepper 
Half a handful of dried shrimp minced finely 
Cook the filling in a pan and wait til cooled to fill the dumplings. 
.
.
.
Dumpling wrapper:
400 g tapioca starch 
2 tbsp vegetable oil
1 tsp salt 
~ 1 cup boiling water 
The first time I hand kneaded it and it was a sticky disaster. This time I used a kitchenaid mixer and it was much easier. Mix on med low while incorporating the hot boiled water. You may need to adjust amount of water as needed until the dough is smooth and elastic but not sticky. (Consistency of play dough). Move dough into a zip lock bag to keep from drying out. Let rest for 15 min. Grab a handful and roll out into a tube shape. Cut into palm sized balls and roll out into 3 mm thickness. 
Place a piece of shrimp in the middle and seal around edges close to the shrimp. Use a small cup to pinch off the excess and make perfect moons. Drop into boiling water and stir to prevent sticking. Once they float to the top cook for another 5 min until edges get more translucent. Strain out into ice water and plate. I made scallion chili oil and nuoc Cham to top. I also garnished with fried onion and @jus_garlic garlic oil. Optional cilantro, mint, basil. 
.
.
.

node.text:
Yep, it's been months since you've seen me and it seems some things have changed! While I was gone I really thought about how I wasn't completely satisfied with my art style, mainly the faces. I'm working on developing that so I haven't made new art for that reason (among others I guess). I have been studying body poses as well, which isn't something I really want to post. Quarantine hasn't really proven helpful when it comes to practicing art, but I'm really working to find motivation to make more content. I can't promise anything, but I have you can hold out through all the changes. Thank you so much everyone and enjoy! ğŸ˜Š
